# ERP Child Form Dialog Standard

## Phase

ERP GLOBAL UI.2 — Apply Standard Child Dialog Design System-Wide (2026-06-14)
ERP GLOBAL UI.4G — Child Form Modal Workspace Blocking and UX Standard Fix (2026-06-14)

## Golden Rules (UI.4G)

1. **ALL ERP child form dialogs MUST use `ERPChildDialogForm`.**
   Any dialog that adds or edits a child record MUST use `ERPChildDialogForm` from
   `@/components/erp/erp-child-dialog-form`. No custom `DialogContent` widths allowed.

2. **Child forms are intentional BLOCKING modal tasks.**
   When a child form is open, workspace tab switching and sidebar/background actions
   are blocked. The user MUST save or cancel the child form before continuing.

3. **Workspace tab bar MUST NOT be clickable while a child form is open.**
   The child dialog overlay (z-[100]) sits above the tab bar (z-[30]).

4. **Sidebar/background MUST NOT be clickable while a child form is open.**
   The full-screen overlay at z-[100] naturally blocks all background interaction.

5. **Parent record content MUST be inert + dimmed while child form is open.**
   Pass `isChildDialogOpen={childDialogOpen}` to `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm`.

6. **Outside click and Esc MUST NOT silently close a child form.**
   `ERPChildDialogForm` blocks all close events not triggered by Cancel/X/Save.

7. **Child forms MUST NOT be converted to workspace record tabs.**
   Main Add/Edit/View forms use `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm`. Child Add/Edit forms use
   `ERPChildDialogForm`. This distinction is non-negotiable.

8. **Combobox/popover inside child dialogs MUST render above child dialog content.**
   `ERPCombobox` dropdown uses `z-[120]` (above dialog content at z-[110]).

---

## The Component

```tsx
import { ERPChildDialogForm } from "@/components/erp/erp-child-dialog-form";

<ERPChildDialogForm
  open={isDialogOpen}
  onOpenChange={setDialogOpen}         // must call both setIsDialogOpen + onChildOpen?.(open)
  title={editing ? "Edit Contact" : "Add Contact"}
  subtitle="Enter contact person details"
  icon={<UserRound className="h-5 w-5" />}
  mode={editing ? "edit" : "add"}      // "add" | "edit" | "view"
  size="lg"                            // default; see size table below
  isSubmitting={isSubmitting}
  onSubmit={handleSubmit}
>
  <div className="grid grid-cols-12 gap-4">
    {/* form fields */}
  </div>
</ERPChildDialogForm>
```

---

## Props Reference

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `open` | `boolean` | — | Dialog open state |
| `onOpenChange` | `(open: boolean) => void` | — | Close/open callback |
| `title` | `string` | — | Header title (required) |
| `subtitle` | `string?` | — | Header subtitle / description |
| `icon` | `ReactNode?` | — | Small icon beside title |
| `mode` | `"add" \| "edit" \| "view"` | `"add"` | Controls submit button label |
| `size` | `"sm" \| "md" \| "lg" \| "xl"` | `"lg"` | Dialog width (see table) |
| `isSubmitting` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables buttons + shows spinner |
| `onCancel` | `() => void?` | — | Pre-cancel callback (rare) |
| `onSubmit` | `() => void?` | — | Primary button click handler |
| `submitLabel` | `string?` | `"Add"` / `"Save"` | Override submit label |
| `cancelLabel` | `string?` | `"Cancel"` | Override cancel label |
| `children` | `ReactNode` | — | Form body content |

---

## Size Tokens

| Token | Max Width | When To Use |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| `sm` | 480px | Confirmation/delete forms, very simple 2–3 field forms |
| `md` | 640px | Admin lookup CRUD forms (≤8 fields, no cascades) |
| `lg` | 960px | **Default.** Standard child forms (contacts, addresses, bank details, licenses) |
| `xl` | 1120px | Complex matrix/table forms — requires justification in PR |

**Default is `lg` (960px). Do not reduce to `md` just because a form is currently short.**

---

## Layout Standard

### Header
- Fixed (does not scroll)
- Icon + Title + optional Subtitle
- Close X button (top right)

### Body
- Scrollable only: `overflow-y-auto flex-1 min-h-0`
- Padding: `p-6` (24px all sides)
- Content: 12-column grid with 16px gap

### Footer
- Sticky (never scrolls)
- Cancel button on **left** (outline variant)
- Submit button on **right** (primary variant)
- Footer padding: `px-6 py-3`

---

## Z-index Standard (UI.4G)

| Layer | Z-index | Notes |
|-------|---------|-------|
| App/page content | base | |
| Workspace tab bar | `z-[30]` | Intentionally below child dialog overlay |
| Record form content | base | |
| Child dialog overlay | `z-[100]` | Full-screen; blocks tab bar and sidebar |
| Child dialog content | `z-[110]` | |
| Combobox/popover inside child dialog | `z-[120]` | |
| Alert/confirm dialog | `z-[130]` | |
| Toast | top layer | |

Child dialog overlay uses: `bg-slate-950/60 backdrop-blur-[2px]`

**DO NOT raise workspace-tab-bar above z-[30].**
**DO NOT set child dialog overlay below z-[100].**

