## Combobox Rule (Rule 14)

**NEVER use shadcn `<Select>` with async-loaded or database-sourced options.**

Shadcn `Select` resolves display labels at mount time. If options load after mount,
the selected value renders as a raw ID instead of the human-readable label.

**Always use `ERPCombobox` for async/database-sourced options:**

```tsx
import { ERPCombobox } from "@/components/erp/combobox";

<ERPCombobox
  value={form.status_id}
  onValueChange={(v) => setForm(f => ({ ...f, status_id: Number(v) }))}
  options={(statuses ?? []).map(s => ({ value: s.id, label: s.name_en }))}
  placeholder="Select status..."
  required
/>
```

---

## Forbidden Patterns

```tsx
// ❌ NEVER — custom DialogContent width for a child form:
<Dialog open={...} onOpenChange={...}>
  <DialogContent className="max-w-2xl max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto">
    ...

// ❌ NEVER — DialogFooter inside the scrollable body area:
<DialogContent className="... overflow-y-auto">
  <div>...fields...</div>
  <DialogFooter>  {/* scrolls with content — WRONG */}
    ...
  </DialogFooter>
</DialogContent>

// ❌ NEVER — inline footer buttons without sticky container:
<div className="flex justify-end gap-2">
  <Button>Cancel</Button>
  <Button>Save</Button>
</div>

// ❌ NEVER — shadcn Select for async data:
<Select value={form.type_id} onValueChange={...}>
  <SelectTrigger>...</SelectTrigger>
  <SelectContent>
    {types.map(t => <SelectItem key={t.id} value={t.id}>{t.name}</SelectItem>)}
  </SelectContent>
</Select>
```

---

## Allowed Exceptions

These dialog types do NOT use `ERPChildDialogForm`:

| Type | Component | Reason |
|------|-----------|--------|
| Delete confirmation | `AlertDialog` | Not a form; uses `AlertDialogContent` |
| Unsaved changes | `AlertDialog` | Not a form |
| Utility/email dialogs | Custom `DialogContent` | Complex custom state; overlay fix applied directly |
| Main standalone CRUD drawers | `ERPDrawerForm` | These are primary add/edit screens, not child forms |

